This paper deals with image perturbations and their effect on image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to achieve imperceptibility, which is a common topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed approaches using experimental data, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
